OL,3,CDoctors held 'outdated' views about
OL,4,CME, inquest into sufferer's death hears
OL,6,FA hospital treating a young woman with
OL,7,Fchronic fatigue was warned a month
OL,8,Fbefore she died about the "dogma" and
OL,9,F"outdated" views some doctors held
OL,10,Fabout the debilitating condition, an
OL,11,Finquest has heard.
OL,13,FDr Willy Weir, a retired NHS
OL,14,Fconsultant and expert in myalgic
OL,15,Fencephalomyelitis (ME), said he urged
OL,16,Fbosses at the Royal Devon and Exeter
OL,17,FHospital (RD&E) to readmit Maeve
OL,18,FBoothby-O'Neill for life-saving
OL,19,Ftreatment.
