OL,3,CDoctors held 'outdated' views about
OL,4,CME, inquest into sufferer's death hears
OL,6,FThe 27-year-old died at home in Exeter
OL,7,Fin October 2021 having suffered with
OL,8,Fthe illness for the previous decade.
OL,10,FThe inquest in Exeter heard Miss
OL,11,FBoothby-O'Neill had been admitted to
OL,12,Fthe hospital three times that year for
OL,13,Ftreatment for malnutrition.
OL,15,FOn the first occasion, in March, she
OL,16,Fwas sent home the same day.
OL,18,FShe was admitted for the second time
OL,19,Fin May and discharged a few weeks
OL,20,Flater with medics content about her
OL,21,Fnutritional intake.
