OL,3,CDoctors held 'outdated' views about
OL,4,CME, inquest into sufferer's death hears
OL,6,FAs she continued to worsen, she was
OL,7,Freadmitted in July to the eating
OL,8,Fdisorder ward but later sent home.
OL,10,FThe hearing is focusing on the last
OL,11,Ffew months of Miss Boothby-O'Neill's
OL,12,Flife by which time she was confined to
OL,13,Fbed, unable to chew food and had
OL,14,Fdifficulty drinking because she was
OL,15,Fnot able to sit up. She was also
OL,16,Funable to read, watch TV or engage in
OL,17,Fconversations.
