OL,3,CDoctors held 'outdated' views about
OL,4,CME, inquest into sufferer's death hears
OL,6,FDr Weir told the hearing he had
OL,7,Fwritten to the chief executive of the
OL,8,Fhospital on 9 September expressing his
OL,9,Fconcerns about her case and the
OL,10,F"outdated" views some doctors held
OL,11,Fabout ME.
OL,13,F"Consequently, patients with this
OL,14,Fcondition have frequently been
OL,15,Fregarded as perversely inactive
OL,16,Fwithout any regard for the possibility
OL,17,Fthat their inactivity is not due to
OL,18,Fdeliberately perverse behaviour," he
OL,19,Fwrote.
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@JO]uD@AOUzD@aO]
