OL,3,CDoctors held 'outdated' views about
OL,4,CME, inquest into sufferer's death hears
OL,6,F"I am fully supportive of this
OL,7,Fapproach, and I am not exaggerating
OL,8,Fthe issue when I say this may well
OL,9,Fsave Maeve's life."
OL,11,FIn hospital Miss Boothby-O'Neill was
OL,12,Ffed for a time through a nasogastric
OL,13,Ftube but due to vomiting it was
OL,14,Fremoved.
OL,16,FDr Weir said had he been responsible
OL,17,Ffor her care he would have considered
OL,18,Ffeeding her directly into the
OL,19,Fintestine, and by increasing her blood
OL,20,Fvolume her movement would have
OL,21,Fimproved.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@SO]
