OL,3,CDoctors held 'outdated' views about
OL,4,CME, inquest into sufferer's death hears
OL,6,F"One of the curious historical facts
OL,7,Fof this illness, although I began to
OL,8,Fbe interested in it in 1987, I never
OL,9,Freally began to see patients as sick
OL,10,Fas Maeve until about 10 or 15 years
OL,11,Fago," Dr Weir said.
OL,13,F"It is almost as if there is some form
OL,14,Fof evolution of this disease process
OL,15,Fwhich is making some people with the
OL,16,Fcondition much more severe.
OL,18,F"It is only when that happens that you
OL,19,Fstart thinking about the things that
OL,20,Fare necessary to keep them alive."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@EO]uD@AOUzD@AOU|D@bO]
