OL,3,CDoctors held 'outdated' views about
OL,4,CME, inquest into sufferer's death hears
OL,6,FMiss Boothby-O'Neill's father Sean
OL,7,FO'Neill, a journalist at The Times,
OL,8,Fasked Dr Weir whether there was still
OL,9,Fresistance within the medical
OL,10,Fprofession to ME being a physical
OL,11,Fillness.
OL,13,F"Until that dogma is properly buried
OL,14,Fand replaced by a proper scientific
OL,15,Funderstanding of this condition within
OL,16,Fthe medical profession as a whole, we
OL,17,Fare not going to progress very far
OL,18,Fwith understanding it and being able
OL,19,Fto treat it properly," he said.
OL,26,@uD@AOU{D@VO]
